ples/\r\rhttp://employeeengagement.ning.com/video/giddyup-employee-engagement- \r\n</p>\r\n<!-- Begin Post -->\r\n<h2 style=\"margin-top:20pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><a  href=\"http://change.mooc.ca/post/507\">Measuring the Wrong Things â€” Has the Scientific Method Been Compromised By Careerism?</a></h2>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:2pt\">\r\n<em><a  href=\"http://change.mooc.ca/cgi-bin/page.cgi?author=Kent Anderson\">Kent Anderson</a>, \r\n<a  href=\"http://change.mooc.ca/cgi-bin/page.cgi?journal=The Scholarly Kitchen\">The Scholarly Kitchen</a>, December 15, 2011.</em><br />\r\nI think this is exactly right: \"Perhaps weâ€™re measuring the wrong things â€” number of publications, number of citations, impact factors of publication outlets â€” as a way of measuring a scientistâ€™s productivity, which we then reward with money, either directly or indirectly. Perhaps we should measure how many results have been replicated. Without that, we are pursuing a cacophony of claims, not cultivating a world of harmonious truths.\" It is not, for example, how many publications I can .... \r\n</p>\r\n<!-- Begin Post -->\r\n<h2 style=\"margin-top:20pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><a  href=\"http://change.mooc.ca/post/505\">Ideas from the thirteen weeks of MOOC</a></h2>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:2pt\">\r\n<em><a  href=\"http://change.mooc.ca/cgi-bin/page.cgi?author=VCVaile\">VCVaile</a>, \r\n<a  href=\"http://change.mooc.ca/cgi-bin/page.cgi?journal=139 - Not Worth Printing\">139 - Not Worth Printing</a>, December 14, 2011.</em><br />\r\na clear, concise overview... hoping it will help me re-orient somewhat and locate the track whether or not I manage to get back on  \r\n</p>\r\n<!-- Begin Post -->\r\n<h2 style=\"margin-top:20pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><a  href=\"http://change.mooc.ca/post/503\">Triangulating, Weaving, and Connecting our Learning</a></h2>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:2pt\">\r\n<em><a  href=\"http://change.mooc.ca/cgi-bin/page.cgi?author=Valerie\">Valerie</a>, \r\n<a  href=\"http://change.mooc.ca/cgi-bin/page.cgi?journal=YouTube\">YouTube</a>, December 14, 2011.</em><br />\r\nNancy White writes, \"As a followup from my week facilitating Change11, the amazing Valerie blew my mind with her video summary and synthesis of the week. No, it was much more than that. WOW. Take a look if you are interested in this idea of the social artist. Valerie, you ROCK!\" Watch it here. See also this earlier video on rhizomatic  \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<!-- FOOTER: Site footer for links, copyright, etc. -->\r\n<div id=\"footer\">\r\n  <div id=\"width\">\r\n    <span class=\"floatLeft\">\r\n<a rel=\"license\" href=\"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/\"><img alt=\"Creative Commons License\" style=\"border-width:0\" src=\"http://i.creativecommons.org/l/by-nc-sa/3.0/88x31.png\" /></a>.\r\n    </span>\r\n\r\n    <span class=\"floatRight\">\r\n<p>Copyright 2011 Stephen Downes, George Siemens, Dave Cormier ~ \r\n\r\n		Contact: <a  href=\"mailto:stephen@downes.ca\">stephen@downes.ca</a><br />\r\nThis page generated by <a  href=\"http://grsshopper.downes.ca\">gRSShopper</a>.  </p>\r\n    </span>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n\r\n</html>\r\n\r\n',NULL,'HTML','page_header','page_footer','yes','no','no','52529',1295294240,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,7,NULL,NULL,'threads.htm',NULL,NULL),(181,'Recordings',NULL,NULL,'htm',NULL,NULL,'<h1>Recordings</h1>\r\n<br/>\r\n<p>On this page we provide links to all the Elluminate recordings from live sessions in the course.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>May 16, Terry Anderson</b><br/>\r\n- <a href=\"http://change.mooc.ca/files/audio/change11_16May2012.mp3\">MP3 Audio</a><br/>\r\n- <a href=\"https://sas.elluminate.com/p.jnlp?psid=2012-05-16.1138.M.3A0EAE843895F0175E240FB3B50AA6.vcr&sid=2008104\">Elluminate Recording</a><br/>\r\n- <a href=\"\r\nhttp://terrya.edublogs.org/2012/05/16/slides-for-change-mooc-may-2012/\">Slides</a>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><b>May 9, Bonnie Stewa