land-Innes</a></br/>\r\n<a  href=\"http://change.mooc.ca/week31.htm\">Week 31: Diana Laurillard</a></br/>\r\n<a  href=\"http://change.mooc.ca/week32.htm\">Week 32: George Siemens</a></br/>\r\n<a  href=\"http://change.mooc.ca/week33.htm\">Week 33: George Veletsianos</a></br/>\r\n<a  href=\"http://change.mooc.ca/week34.htm\">Week 34: Bonnie Stewart</a></br/>\r\n<a  href=\"http://change.mooc.ca/week35.htm\">Week 35: Terry Anderson</a></br/>\r\n</p>\r\n      </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n    <!-- 75 percent width column, aligned to the right -->\r\n    <div class=\"width75 floatRight\">\r\n\r\n\r\n      <!-- Gives the gradient block -->\r\n      <div class=\"gradient\">\r\n\r\n\r\n       <br /><p class=\"login\"> <script language=\"Javascript\">login_box();</script></p><h1>Week 10: Erik Duval</h1>\r\n<h2>Learning in a time of abundance</h2>\r\n<hr>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Live Events</h3>\r\n<p><DATERANGE>2011-11-14 11:00,<END_DATERANGE>: <a  href=\"http://change.mooc.ca/cgi-bin/page.cgi?event=44\">Monday Meeting: Eric Duval</a> - \r\n<b>Live  Session with Eric Duval</b><br>\r\n<p>\r\nThis <a  href=\"https://sas.elluminate.com/m.jnlp?sid=2008104&amp;password=M.C5CCF43B9CF818DDB4113D9A1017A8\">session will be held here</a> in Collaborate (formerly, Elluminate)</p><br/><br/>\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Announcements</h3>\r\n<p><!-- Begin Announcement -->\r\n\r\n<p><b>Week 10: Eric Duval</b><br/>\r\n\r\nThis week we are pleased to welcome Eric Duval as our guest. #week10 Eric is a professor in the research unit on human-computer interaction, at the computer science department of the Katholieke Universiteit Leuven. But what he does extends far beyond that:\r<br/>\r<br/>- president of the <a  href=\"http://www.ariadne-eu.org/\">ARIADNE</a> Foundation\r<br/>- chair of the IEEE LTSC working group on <a  href=\"http://ltsc.ieee.org/wg12/\">Learning Object Metadata</a>\r<br/>- a fellow of the <a  href=\"http://www.aace.org/\">AACE</a>\r<br/>- a member of <a  href=\"http://www.acm.org/\">ACM</a>, and the <a  href=\"http://www.computer.org/\">IEEE computer society</a>\r<br/>- on the Editorial Review Board and the Executive Advisory Board of the <a  href=\"http://www.aace.org/pubs/IJEL/\">International Journal on E-Learning</a>\r<br/>- on the Steering Committee and Editorial Board of the <a  href=\"http://www.computer.org/portal/site/transactions/menuitem.eda2ca84d8d67764cfe79d108bcd45f3/index.jsp?&pName=transactions_level1&path=transactions/tlt/content&file=index.xml&xsl=article.xsl&#eic\">IEEE Transactions on Learning Technologies</a> (TLT)\r<br/>- on the board of editors of the <a  href=\"http://www.jucs.org/jucs_board_of_editors\">Journal of Universal Computer Science</a>\r<br/>- a member of the informatics section of the <a  href=\"http://www.the-academy-of-europe.org/ae/User/Duval_Erik\">Academia Europeae</a>\r<br/>\r<br/>In short, Eric Duval is one of the most influential voices in education technology today, and it is a delight to be able to welcome him to week10 of our course.</p></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Resources</h3>\r\n<p><a  href=\"http://change.mooc.ca/post/359\">Week 10: Erik Duval Learning in a time of abundance</a>\r\nArticle by Duval November 14, 2011<br/>\r\nThe coming week, I will be â€˜facilitatingâ€™ a #change 11 session on â€˜learning in time of abundance\' for week10\r<br/>\r<br/>I put â€˜facilitatingâ€™ between quotes, because I am not completely sure what will happen or what Iâ€™m supposed to do â€“ kind of like what often happens to me in Real Life too  â€¦ As in most courses I â€˜teachâ€™, I expect that I will be the one who learns mostâ€¦\r<br/><br/><br/></p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<strong><a  href=\"http://change.mooc.ca/meetings.htm\">Live Sessions Thursday</a></strong><br />\r\n<a  href=\"?author=Various Authors\">Various Authors</a>, \r\n<a  href=\"?journal=#Change11\">#Change11</a>, November 16, 2011.\r\n--\r<br/>\r<br/><b>COOLCast Session</b>: This week\'s COOLCast will happen on Thursday Nov. 17 at 1500GMT  (that\'s 11:00 a.m. Atlantic, 10:00 a.m. Eastern; global times: http://bit.ly/uUI8WC - one hour before the Elluminate session). Week#10 Facilitator Erik Duval will be joining us. Tune in at <a  href=\"http://www.facebook.com/l/pAQH7ijG_/edtechtalk.com/live\">http://edtechtalk.com/live</a> and join in via Google+ Hangout. #week10\r<br/>\r<br/><b>Live Elluminate Session</b>: The Elluminate Session will be available here starting one hour later (that\'s 12:00 a.m. Atlantic, 11:00 a.m. Eastern, <a  href=\"http://timeanddate.com/worldclock/fixedtime.html?msg=COOLCast+w/+Erik+Duval&iso=20111117T16\">check your time zone</a>). This <a  href=\"https://sas.elluminate.com/m.jnlp?sid=2008104&password=M.C5CCF43B9CF818DDB4113D9A1017A8\">session will be held here</a> in Collaborate (formerly, Elluminate) \r\n\r\n<br /><br /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><keyword db=publication;format=summary;author_name~Duval\r\n\r\n\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<!-- FOOTER: Site footer for links, copyright, etc. -->\r\n<div id=\"footer\">\r\n  <div id=\"width\">\r\n    <span class=\"floatLeft\">\r\n<a rel=\"license\" href=\"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/\"><img alt=\"Creative Commons License\" style=\"border-width:0\" src=\"http://i.creativecommons.org/l/by-nc-sa/3.0/88x31.png\" /></a>.\r\n    </span>\r\n\r\n    <span class=\"floatRight\">\r\n<p>Copyright 2011 Stephen Downes, George Siemens, Dave Cormier ~ \r\n\r\n		Contact: <a  href=\"mailto:stephen@downes.ca\">stephen@downes.ca</a><br />\r\nThis page generated by <a  href=\"http://grsshopper.downes.ca\">gRSShopper</a>.  </p>\r\n    </span>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n\r\n</html>\r\n\r\n',NULL,'HTML','page_header','page_footer','yes','no','no','8810',1321274758,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,7,NULL,NULL,'week10.htm',NULL,NULL),(203,'Week 11: Jon Dron',NULL,NULL,'htm',NULL,NULL,'<h1>Week 11: Jon Dron</h1>\r\n<h2>The Nature of Technologies</h2>\r\n<hr>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Live Events</h3>\r\n<p><keyword db=event;iden