rt, Jon Husband, Harold Jarche, Charles Jennings, &amp; myself\">Internet Time Alliance</a>, and speaks and publishes regularly in the usual places. #week13</p></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Resources</h3>\r\n<p><a  href=\"http://change.mooc.ca/post/417\">Slow Learning</a>\r\nArticle by Clark Quinn December 5, 2011<br/>\r\nOur formal learning approaches too often donâ€™t follow how our brains really work.  We have <em>magic</em> now; we can summon up powerful programs to do our bidding, gaze through webcams across distances, and bring anyone and anything to pretty much anywhere. Our limitations are no longer the technology, but our imaginations. The question is, what are we, and should be, doing with this technology? Also posted <a  href=\"http://blog.learnlets.com/?p=2332\">here</a>. #week13<br/><br/></p>\r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<!-- FOOTER: Site footer for links, copyright, etc. -->\r\n<div id=\"footer\">\r\n  <div id=\"width\">\r\n    <span class=\"floatLeft\">\r\n<a rel=\"license\" href=\"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/\"><img alt=\"Creative Commons License\" style=\"border-width:0\" src=\"http://i.creativecommons.org/l/by-nc-sa/3.0/88x31.png\" /></a>.\r\n    </span>\r\n\r\n    <span class=\"floatRight\">\r\n<p>Copyright 2011 Stephen Downes, George Siemens, Dave Cormier ~ \r\n\r\n		Contact: <a  href=\"mailto:stephen@downes.ca\">stephen@downes.ca</a><br />\r\nThis page generated by <a  href=\"http://grsshopper.downes.ca\">gRSShopper</a>.  </p>\r\n    </span>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n\r\n</html>\r\n\r\n',NULL,'HTML','page_header','page_footer','yes','no','no','10081',1323089984,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,7,NULL,NULL,'week13.htm',NULL,NULL),(206,'Jan Herrington',NULL,NULL,'htm',NULL,NULL,'<h1>Week 14: Jan Herrington</h1>\r\n<h2>Authentic Learning</h2>\r\n<hr>\r\n\r\nTEST\r\n\r\n<h3>Live Events</h3>\r\n<p><keyword db=event;identifier~week14;format=summary;