th75 floatRight\">\r\n\r\n\r\n      <!-- Gives the gradient block -->\r\n      <div class=\"gradient\">\r\n\r\n\r\n       <br /><p class=\"login\"> <script language=\"Javascript\">login_box();</script></p><h1>Week 34: Bonnie Stewart</h1>\r\n<h2>Digital Identities and Subjectivities</h2>\r\n<hr>\r\n\r\n<h3>Announcements</h3>\r\n<p><!-- Begin Announcement -->\r\n\r\n<p><b>Week 34: Bonnie Stewart </b><br/>\r\n\r\n<p>This week we are pleased to welcome Bonnie Stewart to week35 of the course.&nbsp;Bonnie Stewart is a Ph.D. student at the University of Prince Edward Island, Canada. In higher ed since 1997, Bonnie has lived and taught on all three coasts of Canada and in Eastern Europe and Asia. Her research explores social media identity and its implications for higher education. Published at Salon.com and The Guardian UK, and winner of the 2011 PEI Literary Award for creative non-fiction, Bonnie blogs ideas at <a  href=\"http://theory.cribchronicles.com\">http://theory.cribchronicles.com</a> and identity and parenthood at &nbsp;http://cribchronicles.com. Find her on Twitter at @bonstewart.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>This week\'s live online session with Bonnie Stewart: Wednesday May 9 at 11am Eastern&nbsp;The session&nbsp;<a  href=\"https://sas.elluminate.com/site/external/launch/meeting.jnlp?sid=2008104&amp;password=M.C5CCF43B9CF818DDB4113D9A1017A8\">will be held here</a>&nbsp;in Blackboard Collaborate. week34</p></p></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Resources</h3>\r\n<p><a  href=\"http://change.mooc.ca/post/698\">Week 34: Bonnie Stewart Digital Identities</a>\r\nArticle by  May 7, 2012<br/>\r\n<p>Welcome to the home stretch of&nbsp;<a  href=\"../\" target=\"_blank\">#change11</a>, everybody.</p>\r\n<p>This week we&rsquo;ll be looking at digital identities and subjectivities, or &ndash; basically &ndash; who we are in social media spaces.</p>\r\n<p>I&rsquo;m hoping this week will be, above all, a conversation: digital identity is always a lived experience as well as conceptual territory, so everyone has a contribution to offer based on their own practices and experiences. week34</p>\r\n<p><a  href=\"http://theory.cribchronicles.com/2012/05/06/digital-identities-six-key-selves/\">http://theory.cribchronicles.com/2012/05/06/digital-identities-six-key-selves/</a></p><br/><br/></p>\r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<!-- FOOTER: Site footer for links, copyright, etc. -->\r\n<div id=\"footer\">\r\n  <div id=\"width\">\r\n    <span class=\"floatLeft\">\r\n<a rel=\"license\" href=\"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/\"><img alt=\"Creative Commons License\" style=\"border-width:0\" src=\"http://i.creativecommons.org/l/by-nc-sa/3.0/88x31.png\" /></a>.\r\n    </span>\r\n\r\n    <span class=\"floatRight\">\r\n<p>Copyright 2011 Stephen Downes, George Siemens, Dave Cormier ~ \r\n\r\n		Contact: <a  href=\"mailto:stephen@downes.ca\">stephen@downes.ca</a><br />\r\nThis page generated by <a  href=\"http://grsshopper.downes.ca\">gRSShopper</a>.  </p>\r\n    </span>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n\r\n</html>\r\n\r\n',NULL,'HTML','page_header','page_footer','no','no','no','8810',1336432659,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,7,NULL,NULL,'week34.htm',NULL,NULL),(224,'Week 35: Terry Anderson',NULL,NULL,'htm',NULL,NULL,'<h1>Week 35: Terry Anderson</h1>\r\n<h2>Change in formal education systems</h2>\r\n<hr>\r\n\r\n<h3>Announcements</h3>\r\n<p><keyword db=post;type=announcement;format=announcement_summary;description~week35;all;sort=crdate DESC></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Resources</h3>\r\n<p><keyword db=post;number=20;type=article;format=article_summary;description~week35;all;sort=crdate DESC></p>\r\n\r\n<p><keyword db=post;number=20;type=link;format=link_summary;description~week35;all;sort=crdate DESC></p>\r\n\r\n<p><keyword db=publication;format=summary;author_name~Anderson</p>\r\n\r\n<keyword db=presentation;format=html;description~week35;all;sort=crdate DESC>','Friday','<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC 