. More specifically, he studies Adventure Learning, pedagogical agents, and Networked Participatory Scholarship. week33</p>\r\n<p>This week\'s live online session with George Veletsianos: Wednesday May 2 at 1pm Eastern (<a  href=\"http://www.timeanddate.com/worldclock/fixedtime.html?iso=20120502T13&amp;p1=250\">Check your time zone</a>) The session <a  href=\"https://sas.elluminate.com/site/external/launch/meeting.jnlp?sid=2008104&amp;password=M.C5CCF43B9CF818DDB4113D9A1017A8\">will be held here</a> in Blackboard Collaborate.</p></p></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Resources</h3>\r\n<p><a  href=\"http://change.mooc.ca/post/691\">Scholarsâ€™ participation and practices online</a>\r\nArticle by George Veletsianos April 30, 2012<br/>\r\n<p>This week, I&rsquo;d like us to think about scholars&rsquo; participation and practices online. We will examine this topic by discussing research that I have conducted on the topic, reflecting on our own practice, and synthesizing information already discussed in the #change11 MOOC. week33</p><br/><br/></p>\r\n\r\n<p></p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<!-- FOOTER: Site footer for links, copyright, etc. -->\r\n<div id=\"footer\">\r\n  <div id=\"width\">\r\n    <span class=\"floatLeft\">\r\n<a rel=\"license\" href=\"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/\"><img alt=\"Creative Commons License\" style=\"border-width:0\" src=\"http://i.creativecommons.org/l/by-nc-sa/3.0/88x31.png\" /></a>.\r\n    </span>\r\n\r\n    <span class=\"floatRight\">\r\n<p>Copyright 2011 Stephen Downes, George Siemens, Dave Cormier ~ \r\n\r\n		Contact: <a  href=\"mailto:stephen@downes.ca\">stephen@downes.ca</a><br />\r\nThis page generated by <a  href=\"http://grsshopper.downes.ca\">gRSShopper</a>.  </p>\r\n    </span>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n\r\n</html>\r\n\r\n',NULL,'HTML','page_header','page_footer','yes','no','no','10081',1337172726,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,7,NULL,NULL,'week33.htm',N